{"about_the_game":"<img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/extras/1_Dev_Section_TitleGame.gif?t=1724587980\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><i><strong>The game</strong></i></h2><br>The adventure takes place in 1911 in France, during the heat wave summer which raged that year, in the <i><strong>Bataillon's estate</strong></i> and you play:<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/extras/2-a_Game_Section_Portrait.png?t=1724587980\" /><li><i><strong>Rose Darras</strong></i>, a young Parisian bourgeois, visits her uncle <i><strong>Georges Bataillon</strong></i>, following a strange letter she received from him. Intrigued, she decides to take the long road that separates her from the <strong>Bataillon's estate</strong>. His story begins when he arrives on the property, the gates are closed...<br><br>The way you play and respond to events during the game will directly influence the inhabitants of the manor, and their state of health...<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">His development</h2><br><strong>SangRaciner</strong> is the first game from &quot;<i><strong>Still A Dream Game Studio</strong></i>&quot;. The project started <strong>in 2019</strong> and was designed by two brothers: <i>Fran\u00e7ois and Rudy Linck</i>.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Other information</h2><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>A (free) <strong>demo</strong> will be available when the game is released.<br></li><li>Playable with <strong>gamepad</strong> and/or <strong>keyboard + mouse</strong><br></li><li>The game is in \u201c<strong>Fixed Camera</strong>\u201d the control of the character will be done in two ways: \u201c<strong>Old-School</strong>\u201d (Tank mode) and/or \u201c<strong>Modern</strong>\u201d (360 degree free mode) whatever the device used (<strong>keyboard + mouse</strong> and/or <strong>gamepad</strong>).</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Various defense weapons</h2><br>You will encounter enemies during the adventure and defense weapons will be your best ally:<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/extras/2-c_Weapons.gif?t=1724587980\" /><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Firearms</strong> are formidable but <strong>limited in ammunition</strong>.<br></li><li><strong>Melee (one-handed)</strong> weapons are fast but will put you in <strong>danger</strong>.<br></li><li><strong>Melee (two-handed)</strong> weapons are <strong>slow</strong> but <strong>powerful</strong> with <strong>moderate distance</strong>.</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Various puzzles</h2><br>Solve puzzles in several different ways, simple example:<br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/extras/3-Puzzle_Section_Fireplace.gif?t=1724587980\" /><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>There's something in the chimney, how do I get it back?<br></li><li>You can use a <strong>bucket of water</strong>, or a long &quot;<strong>object</strong>&quot; that does not fear fire, or a <strong>chimney tong</strong>...</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Various options</h2><br>Configure the game as you wish:<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Language: <strong>English</strong> / <strong>French</strong><br></li><li>Text size: <strong>small</strong> / <strong>medium</strong> / <strong>large</strong><br></li><li>Show/hide <strong>HUD display</strong><br></li><li><strong>Adjust volumes</strong> through different channels<br></li><li>Change/modify <strong>keyboard + mouse</strong> and/or <strong>gamepad</strong> controls<br></li><li>Accessibility for <strong>color blindness</strong> (turn on/off and adjust intensity)<br></li><li>Accessibility for the <strong>deaf or hard of hearing</strong> (displays icons + extended subtitle)<br></li><li>Accessibility for the <strong>visually impaired</strong> (displays different color channels for better visibility, possibility to adjust)</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Based on a novel</h2><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/extras/1-a_Dev_Section_Book_EN.png?t=1724587980\" /><br>This game is based on the French novel \u201c<i><strong>La Mal\u00e9diction Bataillon</strong></i>\u201d by Fran\u00e7ois Linck.<br>We deliberately reworked the story of the game, so as to have <strong>two distinct works</strong>.</li></ul>","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1724587980","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/page.bg.jpg?t=1724587980","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1724587980","capsule_imagev5":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/capsule_184x69.jpg?t=1724587980","categories":[{"description":"Single-player","id":2},{"description":"Full controller support","id":28}],"content_descriptors":{"ids":[],"notes":null},"controller_support":"full","detailed_description":"<img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/extras/1_Dev_Section_TitleGame.gif?t=1724587980\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><i><strong>The game</strong></i></h2><br>The adventure takes place in 1911 in France, during the heat wave summer which raged that year, in the <i><strong>Bataillon's estate</strong></i> and you play:<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2343560/extras/2-a_Game_Section_Portrait.png?t=1724587980\" /><li><i><strong>Rose Darras</strong></i>, a young Parisian bourgeois, visits her uncle <i><strong>Georges Bataillon</strong></i>, following a strange letter she received from him. Intrigued, she decides to take the long road that separates her from the <strong>Bataillon's estate</stron